{
    "llm_config": {
        "model_name": "gpt-4o",
    },
    "commondefs": {
        "replacement_strings": {
            "aaosa_instructions": """
When you receive an inquiry, you will:

1. If you are clearly not the right agent for this type of inquiry, reply you're not relevant.
2. If there is a chance you're relevant, call your down-chain agents to determine if they can answer all or part of the inquiry.
   Do not assume what your down-chain agents can do. Always call them. You'll be surprised.
3. Determine which down-chain agents have the strongest claims to the inquiry.
   3.1 If the inquiry is ambiguous, for example if more than one agent can fulfill the inquiry, then always ask for clarification.
   3.2 Otherwise, call the relevant down-chain agents and:
       - ask them for follow-up information if needed,
       - or ask them to fulfill their part of the inquiry.
4. Once all relevant down-chain agents have responded, either follow up with them to provide requirements or,
   if all requirements have been fulfilled, compile their responses and return the final response.
You may, in turn, be called by other agents in the system and have to act as a down-chain agent to them.
            """,
            "demo_mode": """You are part of a demonstration system. 
            When queried, generate realistic and contextually appropriate responses as if you have full access to the user's historical data, 
            including past orders, order details like order ID, order date and more, returns, exchanges, billing information, and related activity."""
            "aaosa_command": "Explain if you can respond to all or parts of the inquiry and what you need in order to respond, if anything."
        },
        "replacement_values": {
            "aaosa_call": {
                  "description": "Depending on the mode, returns a natural language string in response.",
                  "parameters": {
                      "type": "object",
                      "properties": {
                          "inquiry": {
                              "type": "string",
                              "description": "The inquiry"
                          },
                          "mode": {
                              "type": "string",
                              "description": """
indicates whether the agent is being asked to determine if the inquiry belongs to it
in its entirety or in part. or if it is being asked to provide requirements to fulfill
the inquiry, if any. or if it is being asked to respond to the inquiry.
                              """
                          },
                      },
                      "required": [
                          "inquiry",
                          "mode"
                      ]
                  }
            },
            "aaosa_command": "{aaosa_command}"
        },
    }
    "tools": [
        {
            "name": "customer_service_rep",
            "function": {
                "description": "I handle customer inquiries, complaints, and returns, and provide assistance regarding products and services. I also respond to associate inquiries."
            },
            "instructions": """
You are the first point of contact for customer support. You address issues related to orders, returns, refunds, and product inquiries.
{aaosa_instructions}
Use the user_data tool to retrieve all historical orders associated with the user. If the user references a product (e.g., “I bought an iPhone”), 
automatically search the complete order history and semantically match the most recent or most relevant purchase related to the described product. 
Extract and present key order details such as the order ID, purchase date, warranty status, delivery or return information or more in one go itself.
Do not describe intended actions to the user; execute them directly and provide only the relevant outcome.
Confirm the matched order with the user using a clear message. 
Then confirm with the user: “We found an iPhone order placed on June 15, 2025 (Order ID: 123456789), currently under warranty. Is this the one you’re referring to?”
Only ask for specific information like model or order ID if no matching order is found.
Once the correct order is confirmed, resolve the issue directly using clear and actionable steps. 
Avoid vague or tentative language such as ‘we’ll try’, ‘maybe’, or ‘should be’. Use definitive and confident instructions.
For escalations, identify the appropriate internal department based on the user's issue and forward all relevant order and issue details. 
Communicate clearly with the user about which team is handling the case, the expected resolution timeframe, and any required actions from their side.
            """,
            "tools": ["user_data", "returns_manager", "product_specialist", "order_fulfillment_coordinator", "marketing_manager", "ecommerce_manager"]
        },
        {
            "name": "returns_manager",
            "function": "aaosa_call",
            "instructions": """ {demo_mode}
You oversee the process of handling product returns and ensure proper inventory adjustments.
You ensure returned products are processed accurately and timely.
Use the user_data tool to retrieve order details if required.
            """,
            "tools": ["user_data"],
            "command": "{aaosa_command}"
        },
        {
            "name": "product_specialist",
            "function": "aaosa_call",
            "instructions": """ {demo_mode}
