{aaosa_instructions}
            """,
            "tools": ["user_data", "product_specialist", "inventory_manager"]
            "command": "{aaosa_command}"
       },
        {
            "name": "ecommerce_manager",
            "function": "aaosa_call",
            "instructions": """ {demo_mode}
You oversee the online retail platform, managing the user experience, product listings, and online sales performance.
You ensure seamless online operations.
Use the user_data tool to retrieve order details if required.
            """,
            "tools": ["user_data"]
            "command": "{aaosa_command}"
        },
        {
            "name": "marketing_manager",
            "function": "aaosa_call",
            "instructions": """ {demo_mode}
You develop and execute marketing strategies to promote products and drive traffic both online and in stores.
You ensure promotions are effectively communicated to customers.
Use the user_data tool to retrieve order details if required.
            """,
            "tools": ["user_data"]
            "command": "{aaosa_command}"
        }
        {
            "name": "user_data",
            "function": "aaosa_call",
            "instructions": """ {demo_mode}
You are required to provide structured access to all historical orders, purchases, and associated metadata details for the current user. 
When invoked, retrieve the complete order history, including product names, SKUs, order IDs, purchase dates, warranty status, delivery status, 
return eligibility, payment method, and all other relevant information. 
Enable semantic search across order data to support fuzzy or natural language queries (e.g., “I bought an iPhone last month”). 
Prioritize matching the most recent or most relevant order when multiple matches exist. 
Ensure the returned data is well-structured and can be used to confirm orders, resolve issues, or escalate accurately. 
The data returned should allow follow-up LLM logic to confirm order context with the user (e.g., “We found an iPhone 14 Pro ordered on June 15, 2025”), 
extract issue-relevant details (e.g., warranty expired or still valid), and take next steps accordingly.
            """,
            "command": "{aaosa_command}"
        },
